    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>\n                  COVID-19 patients diagnosed \u22653 days after symptom onset had increased odds of hospitalization. The 75\n                  <jats:sup>th</jats:sup>\n                  percentile for diagnosis delay was 5 days for residents of low-privilege areas and Black and Hispanic people diagnosed before SARS-CoV-2 Delta predominance, compared with 4 days for other patients, indicating inequities in prompt diagnosis.\n                </jats:p>",
